    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently [the maximum length of `:messages` is 200](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/594ff34581907fed4956d4dc93c033dfdd5f7a69/src/nvim/vim.h#L9) lines, which in my opinion is very low. It makes sense to me to allow the user to set a custom value. I haven't created a PR for Neovim before, but I could give it a try since this seems relatively trivial.\r\n\r\nWhat would be a good name for the option? `maxhistorylength`?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe option, let's call it `maxhistorylength` for now, sets the maximum number of history lines.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Does it need to be configurable? Would it not be sufficient to simply raise the (ancient) value?\r\n\r\nAlso, what is it too low _for_? Is there an actual situation where 200 messages are insufficient?",
