        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That is useful context, thank you. But for such large output, wouldn't you rather `:put` it in a buffer?\r\n\r\n(The long-term goal is to stop unconditionally shoving everything into a single `:messages` area and instead allow different routing for messages depending on type.)\r\n\r\nWould it be an alternative to expand the `vim.print` function to optionally specify an output buffer/split?",
