        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@clason \r\n\r\n> wouldn't you rather :put it in a buffer\r\n\r\nWith [noice.nvim](https://github.com/folke/noice.nvim) I already get `:messages` in a buffer, but with less effort.\r\n\r\n> The long-term goal is to stop unconditionally shoving everything into a single `:messages` area\r\n>\r\n> Would it be an alternative to expand the `vim.print` function to optionally specify an output buffer/split?\r\n\r\nBoth of these sound like good ideas but I still think that 200 is way too low, and like you say it is up to personal taste what is _too low_. Therefore it makes sense to me to allow the maximum value to be configured by the user.",
